		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-name">
			<h1 class="show-h1">
				Norway
			</h1>
		</div>
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-lesson">
			<h5 class="show-h5">
				Lesson 9
			</h5>
		</div>
			
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<img class="show-flag" src="https://cdn.britannica.com/01/3101-004-506325BB/Flag-Norway.jpg">
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-firstquickfacth4'>
			<h4>Capital: Oslo</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Population: 5.3 million</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP): 403 billion dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP) Per Capita: 75,000 dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<hr class="show-hr1">	
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1 show-map" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Norway_in_Europe_%28-rivers_-mini_map%29.svg/1198px-Norway_in_Europe_%28-rivers_-mini_map%29.svg.png">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Kingdom of Norway is a Nordic country roughly the same size of Mexico. Norway was settled around 872. The name Norway was from an Old English word Norþweg, which means “the northern way”. Norway was a part of Denmark-Norway Union between 1537 to 1814, after which in entered another Union with Kingdom of Sweden until 1905. Although Norway remained neutral during the First World War, it was invaded and occupied by Germany in 1940 until the end of Second World War.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today is a constitutional monarchy that has a universal healthcare system, which means free healthcare for everyone. It also has the lowest crime rate, one of the highest income per capita, and continuously ranks first in World Happiness Report.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://resize-parismatch.lanmedia.fr/img/var/news/storage/images/paris-match/brouillons/harald-v-sonja-haakon-mette-marit-en-photos-la-famille-royale-de-norvege-se-refait-les-portraits-899315/9533343-1-fre-FR/La-famille-de-Norvege-se-refait-les-portraits.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Norweigen Royal family</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Norway’s climate is somewhat mild considering its location. The coastal regions being more mild than inland regions with temperatures above freezing even in polar winter nights.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Geographically Norway is known for its fjords, which are flooded valleys created by retreating glaciers. Norway is often described as the“Land of the Midnight Sun”. During the summer months between May and late July, the sun never never drops below the horizon in the Northern part of the country.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="http://res.cloudinary.com/simpleview/image/upload/v1470836048/clients/norway/naeroyfjorden_fjord_norway_2_1_001b9127-14ad-4b3d-99b6-29d8b3aae412.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Fjord valleys of Norway</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Norway has a diverse land and marine animal life. Some of the wild life found on land are Polar Bear, Arctic Fox, and Gray Wolf. The biggest predator in Norwegian waters is the Sperm Whale, while Basking Shark is the biggest fish in these waters.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d774e786b6a4d30457a6333566d54/img/458f5dfbaaf54c318e3c32870bca6419/458f5dfbaaf54c318e3c32870bca6419.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Sperm Whales are the largest predators in Norweigan waters</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Norway’s capital city is Oslo. Norwegians speak Norwegian (a Germanic language derived from Old Norse), and Sami. Norway’s currency is Norwegian Krone (NOR). Norway’s biggest industry is petroleum and natural gas.

			</p>
		</div>
	
		
		

		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<h3 class="show-factsh3">
				Two unique facts about Norway
			</h3>
		</div>
			
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The troll plays a significant part in Norse mythology. The trolls are ugly creatures that lives in small families in caves, mountains or rocks and turn into rock if the sun light hits them.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
	
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				On the remote Norwegian Island of Svalbard, scientists stored over 2 billion seeds of vegetables, grains, and flowers in a vault deep underground in case of a global disaster. These seeds are stored in low temperatures and can survive for thousands of years. So if there was a disaster, Norway would will be the ultimate superhero and rescue the world!

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://images.newscientist.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/24221112/seed-vault-exterior_49556085172_o_web.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Svalbard doomsday vault contains over 2 billion seeds</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
